{
  "texts": [
    "Numeric DocIDs, however, do not offer this advantage.",
    "Thus, as mentioned in 6.1.1, extensive pre-training is necessary to enable models to fully understand the meanings behind these numerical strings, which is a costly endeavor.Do We Need a Unique ID for Each Document?",
    "Most current GR methods use a unique DocID to uniquely identify a document.",
    "However, as the number of documents in a corpus increases, maintaining a unique DocID becomes increasingly challenging.",
    "Even if a unique DocID is maintained, it is difficult to differentiate significantly from other DocIDs semantically, leading to reduced retrieval precision."
  ]
}